Follow the step if you loose access to your user or root in Ubuntu26.04

STEP 1
Reboot your system and continuously press the interupt key (usually esc or f12) to enter bios 
Select 'Advanced options for Ubuntu' and enter. This opens the GNU GRUB menu
Select 'Recovery mode' Option. When this loads you will be prompted with a Recovery menu
Select 'Root'
Once at the # prompt, ensure the partition is writable
bash 'mount -o remount.rw /
Update the password accordingly and re-boot the system
